### Hadith 1:19

*Narrated 'Aisha:*

Whenever Allah's Apostle ordered the Muslims to do something, he used to
order them deeds which were easy for them to do, (according to their
strength endurance). They said, "O Allah's Apostle! We are not like you.
Allah has forgiven your past and future sins." So Allah's Apostle became
angry and it was apparent on his face. He said, "I am the most Allah
fearing, and know Allah better than all of you do."

